President Biden has declared a state of emergency in Texas due to the severe winter storm that began on February 11, 2021. This declaration allows the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to coordinate disaster relief efforts and provide assistance to alleviate the hardship caused by the emergency. FEMA is authorized to identify, mobilize, and provide necessary equipment and resources to mitigate the impacts of the emergency. Emergency protective measures and direct federal assistance will be provided at 75 percent federal funding. Jerry S. Thomas has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas. For further information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.